## FireCut v1.2.4 JavaScript Deobfuscation Analysis

### File Location
`/Users/imorgado/Desktop/FireCut_v1.2.4/com.firecut.base/lib/zooms/main.js`

---

## 1. Main Functions and Purpose

This file implements a **zoom and transcript manipulation system** for the FireCut Adobe Premiere Pro plugin. It provides:

- **Transcript text display and editing** with word-level granularity
- **Zoom animation management** synchronized with video transcripts
- **Interactive highlight/selection system** for creating and editing zooms
- **Bidirectional sync** between frontend UI and backend Adobe Premiere Pro clips

### Main Classes

#### ZoomsHighlight Class
Represents a single zoom highlight segment with time boundaries:
```javascript
class ZoomsHighlight {
  constructor(start, end, startBreakpoints, endBreakpoints, confirmed, nodeId) {
    this.start = start;
    this.end = end;
    this.startBreakpoints = startBreakpoints;
    this.endBreakpoints = endBreakpoints;
    this.confirmed = confirmed || false;
    this.nodeId = nodeId || '';
  }

  get firstWordPos() { /* returns index of first word */ }
  get lastWordPos() { /* returns index of last word */ }
}
```

#### ZoomsTranscript Class
Main controller managing the entire zoom/transcript workflow:
```javascript
class ZoomsTranscript {
  constructor(transcript, zooms, defaultZoomParams, rtl, videoFrameRate) {
    this.transcript = transcript;
    this.zooms = zooms;
    this.defaultZoomParams = defaultZoomParams;
    this.videoFrameRate = videoFrameRate;
    this.rtl = rtl; // Right-to-left language support
    // 35+ initialization methods called in constructor
  }
}
```

