## 4. Key Algorithms and Logic

### Transcript Quantization
Aligns word/segment timestamps to video frame boundaries:
```javascript
quantizeTranscript() {
  this.transcript.segments.forEach(segment => {
    segment.start = Math.round(segment.start / this.videoFrameRate) * this.videoFrameRate;
    segment.end = Math.round(segment.end / this.videoFrameRate) * this.videoFrameRate;

    segment.words.forEach(word => {
      word.start = Math.round(word.start / this.videoFrameRate) * this.videoFrameRate;
      word.end = Math.round(word.end / this.videoFrameRate) * this.videoFrameRate;
    });
  });
}
```

### Zoom Clips Change Listener
Monitors for clip changes in Premiere and syncs back to UI:
```javascript
async zoomClipsChangeListener() {
  while (true) {
    await delay(500); // Poll every 500ms

    const clipsInPremiere = await getZoomClipsAccordingToSequence(this.zooms);

    // Compare with local state
    this.zooms.forEach(localZoom => {
      const clip = clipsInPremiere.find(c => c.nodeId === localZoom.nodeId);
      if (clip) {
        // Update timing
        localZoom.word_indices = getWordIndicesFromTimeRegion([clip.start, clip.end]);
      } else {
        // Clip deleted in Premiere
        localZoom.deleted = true;
      }
    });
  }
}
```

### Word-Level Selection Tracking
Converts character selections to word indices:
```javascript
selectionRangeToTotalOffset(range) {
  // Accumulate character offsets from line lengths
  let startOffset = range.startOffset;
  for (let i = 0; i < lineIndex; i++) {
    startOffset += this.lineLengths[i];
  }
  return { totalStartOffset, totalEndOffset };
}
```

### Handle Dragging (Left/Right Boundaries)
Allows users to resize zoom regions by dragging handles:
```javascript
initLeftHandles() {
  $('.zooms-handle-left-hitbox').on('mousedown', (e) => {
    const handleId = $(e.target).data('handleid');
    const currentEnd = this.highlights[handleId].end;

    // Track mouse movement
    $(window).on('mousemove', () => {
      const selection = window.getSelection();
      const newStart = getClosestWordBreakpoint(selection);

      if (newStart < currentEnd) {
        this.highlights[handleId].start = newStart;
        this.loadTranscriptOverlay(); // Redraw
      }
    });
  });
}
```

